"title": "2039: Jesus Christ, joy of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2039: jesus christ, joy of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ brings joy to his people, who are able to rejoice at the coming of their Saviour and Lord, and all the benefits which he brings to them.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's joy originates in God</h2>\n<h3>From his intimate relationship with his Father and the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25-Matt11:26\">MAT 11:25–11:26</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:2-Isa11:3\">ISA 11:2–11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16-Matt3:17\">MAT 3:16–3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10-Mark1:11\">MRK 1:10–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:18\">MAT 12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:28\">ACT 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:11\">PSA 16:11</a></p>\n<h3>From his awareness of God's purposes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:29\">JHN 8:29</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's coming brings great joy</h2>\n<h3>His birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:10-Luke2:11\">LUK 2:10–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:10\">MAT 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:44\">LUK 1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:20\">LUK 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:28-Luke2:32\">LUK 2:28–2:32</a></p>\n<h3>His resurrection and ascension</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:20-John16:22\">JHN 16:20–16:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:8-Matt28:9\">MAT 28:8–28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:40-Luke24:41\">LUK 24:40–24:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:50-Luke24:53\">LUK 24:50–24:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:20\">JHN 20:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ gives joy to his people</h2>\n<h3>He brings joy to his disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:13\">JHN 17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:3\">ISA 61:1–61:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:11\">JHN 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:12\">ROM 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:26\">PHP 1:26</a></p>\n<h3>Being in his presence is likened to the joy of a wedding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:1-Matt22:10\">MAT 22:1–22:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:14-Matt9:15\">MAT 9:14–9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18-Mark2:19\">MRK 2:18–2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33-Luke5:34\">LUK 5:33–5:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1-Matt25:10\">MAT 25:1–25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:29\">JHN 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a></p>\n<h3>To know Jesus Christ brings great joy to others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:7\">LUK 15:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:10\">LUK 15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:22-Luke15:24\">LUK 15:22–15:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:31-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:31–15:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:56\">JHN 8:56</a></p>",
